Encryption-Decryption

Program is used to encrypt and decrypt String values
It is designed to work from terminal commands
Also supports reading and writing into files

List of supported arguments,
arguments may be entered in any order:

-mode [enc] [dec] || encode and decode mode (encode by default)
-alg [shift] [unicode] || type of algorithm to use (shift by default)
-key [Integer] || value by witch algorithm makes encryption and decryption
-data [String] || data that will be processed
-in [File path] || File to read from
-out [File path] || File to wright to

Example : java Main -mode enc -key 5 -data "Welcome to hyperskill!" -alg unicode
Result : \jqhtrj%yt%m~ujwxpnqq&